item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: About me
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded: I have capturing images for over 20 years after studying photography at college. Sometimes it hard to think this is a job when I love it so much and have so much passion for this art. I am from East London originally, which is where my studio is located, but now I live in South East London with my wife and children. Family is important to me. I like to travel and document in photography my family adventures as well as the up and downs of life. Capturing people moments is thrilling and exciting as you never know what I will freeze in time and then that moment is there forever not only in memory, but visually whether electronically or print. I love those happy moments child smiling, proud father at his daughters wedding or families coming together, its what i love in my life and makes me happy photographing this for my clients. My style is candid natural images, those moments people may take for granted, but can look back on and smile and formal photos showing the present family tree. My ethos is honesty and providing an excellent service to all my clients no matter the budget spent or the event you have hired me for.

"Any moment in your life I am happy to capture for you"

My aim is for you to look back on your images and remember what actually happened on your wedding day, not what was set-up. I want the atmosphere and emotion to shine through each and every image. A wedding day goes by so quickly but what will live on in the months and years after, are the memories, and the images.

To check my availability and to enquire about my full range of coverage options, please do get in touch, Iâ€™d love to hear all about your plans.
